Everfrost - has stuff you can hunt all the way up to level 40 (not that I am saying stay there the whole time, but you could, and its so close to your home).<br>
<br>
GFay - Overcrowded, and /auc spam is nonstop, but it is one of the best newbie zones in the game.  The orcs are plentiful.  Plus, there is Crushbone right nearby, a pretty good dungeon up to level 17 or so.<br>
<br>
Butcherblock Mnts - lots of hunting here, from levels 1 to 15.  Goblin camps (1 to 8th level) Chessboard (up to 12th or so), plenty of wandering monsters (drakes, basilisks, named Ogres), and a nice Orc camp (up to level 15).  Lots of nearby guards to run to.<br>
<br>
East CommonLands / South Ro - both good zones with plenty of monsters (Bears, firebeetles, various snakes for your waterpets, zombies, madmen, on and on).  Good exp, you can go up to 12th level here.<br>
<br>
Steamfont - Great for using that ward summoned spell against wandering Earth Elementals.  Levels 1 to 6, use the newbie zone near the druid ring, it is pretty safe there, and its not usually overhunted.  You can also pay a Druid to port you directly to this newbie zone from your home town.   After the newbie are greens out, you can adventure near the mino caves (Earth Elementals, Drakes, Skellies, Mino Slavers, rogue Clockworks, on and on) up to level 14 or 15.<br>
 <p></b>Seek Pyremaker</b><br>
